<p>Under no immune selection, the probability of glycosylation at site 
 <italic>i</italic> was calculated by finding the probability of having the Asn−
 <italic>X</italic>−Ser/Thr sequon [
 <xref rid="pcbi.1007892.ref039" ref-type="bibr">39</xref>] (where 
 <italic>X</italic> is not proline) assuming site independence. This assumption is necessary and implicit as DMS data only consider single residue changes on a specific background HA protein. In particular, these data do not consider epistatic interactions between residues, including any such interactions that would enrich Asn−
 <italic>X</italic>−Ser/Thr sequons. Therefore, the estimate of the glycosylation probability at site 
 <italic>i</italic> is 
